div.div: Dungeon ni Deai wo Motomeru no wa Machigatteiru Darou ka IV: Shin Shou Meikyuu-hen

The fourth season of Dungeon ni Deai wo Motomeru no wa Machigatteiru Darou ka. Intrepid adventurer Bell Cranel has leveled up, but he can’t rest on his dungeoneering laurels just yet. The Hestia Familia still has a long way to go before it can stand toe-to-toe with the other Familias of Orario — but before Bell can set out on his next mission, reports of a brutal murder rock the adventuring community! One of Bell’s trusted allies stands accused of the horrible crime, and it’s up to Bell and his friends to clear their name and uncover a nefarious plot brewing in the dungeon’s dark depths. (Source: Sentai Filmworks)

The second season of Yakusoku no Neverland. Fifteen children escape Grace Field House, a false paradise, hoping for a chance at freedom. Instead, they encounter plants and animals they have never before seen, and are chased by demons. The outside world is so beautiful, and yet is almost too cruel to face. Even so, the children refuse to give up. They are guided in their search for better lives only by a message from Minerva and a pen Norman left behind in order to fulfill their promise to return to the House to save those of their family who are still trapped within.
(Source: Aniplex of America) Note: Episode 1 streamed early on Amazon Prime on Jan 7, 2021. The regular TV broadcast started on Jan 8, 2021.
Seijo no Hazu ga, Douyara Nottoraremashita
Comedy, Fantasy, Romance, Slice of Life

“Will you save us? YES or NO?”

In standard dating sim style, “Anise” was summoned as a Saint into the world of “Garden of Salvation”. However, Hime, another girl who was also summoned alongside her, stole the title of “Saint” for herself! Without being allowed to use the “healing magic” that she had learned, Anise was exiled to a remote village. If things stick to the script, a general from the neighboring kingdom of Farglow will die before long and Hime will reign supreme as the Saint in the bad ending. For Anise, that means death. In order to find her own path for survival, she decides to save the general and rewrite the story, but…

(Source: MangaUP!)

Sold off by her mother, a young girl winds up in the house of the empire’s most feared duke, Ein Castielo. Given the name Estelle, she must come to terms with her family, demon-lineage, and new standing in high society. But what will happen to the innocent Estelle when the enemies of the duke learn of her existence? Does she really have what it takes to be a child of the great and powerful Castielos?
(Source: Tapas)

div.span: Turbulent Adventurers are Introverted, Observant, Feeling, Prospecting and Turbulent. Adventurers are flexible and charming, always ready to explore and experience something new. They tend to have open minds, approaching life, new experiences, and people with grounded warmth.
Mostly Introverted. Likely prefers fewer, yet deep and meaningful, social interactions and feels drawn to calmer environments.
Mostly Observant. Likely pragmatic and down-to-earth, with a strong focus on what is happening or very likely to happen.
Mostly Feeling. Likely values emotional expression and sensitivity, prioritizing empathy, social harmony, and cooperation.
Mostly Prospecting. Likely very good at improvising and adapting. Tends to be flexible and values novelty above stability.
Mostly Turbulent. Likely self-conscious, sensitive to stress, success-driven, perfectionistic, and eager to improve.
